        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "5bd8f72d1ecad7f8efe7156f3e15790d6df90386",
            "subject": "LU-4423 lnet: remove LNET_MUTEX_LOCK macro"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "vinayakswami hariharmath",
          "email": "vinayakswami.hariharmath@seagate.com",
          "date": "2015-11-04 07:25:32.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "vinayakswami hariharmath",
          "email": "vinayakswami.hariharmath@seagate.com",
          "date": "2016-04-09 06:01:52.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "subject": "LU-5216 hsm: restore doesn't restart for new copytool",
        "message": "LU-5216 hsm: restore doesn't restart for new copytool\n\nThis patch handles:\n\n1. Unexpected client (data mover node) eviction could\ncause on going hsm requests to be stuck in \"STARTED\"\nstate as the copy tool running on the data mover node\nis no more available. This patch unregisters the\ncopy tool and cancels all the requests on the copy\ntool agent.\n\n2. The way to stop copy tool is to KILL it. In this\ncase also, as above explained, on going hsm operations\nget stuck in \"STARTED\" state and if any other copy tool\ntries to do any hsm activity  on that file will not be\nprocessed as the hsm operation on that file still going\non. Such stuck operations will be cleared after request\ntime out but we need handle this immediately once the\ncopy tool agent dies, so that other copy tool can process\nsmoothly. Patch will handle this situation by waiting for\nthe on going hsm activity to complete and free the request.\nWe need to wait for the request complete and return to\nmake sure that the hsm operation should not be blocked.\n\nAdding test_61 to sanity-hsm.sh to verify the fix\n\nSeagate-bug-id: MRP-2464\nSigned-off-by: vinayakswami hariharmath <vinayakswami.hariharmath@seagate.com>\nChange-Id: I611775f93029805644dbf486050e59c7836c91e1\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
